text: Tridrepana spatulata is a moth in the family Drepanidae. It was described by Allan Watson in 1957. It is found on Luzon and Mindanao in the Philippines. The wingspan is about 31–35 mm for males and about 38.5 mm for females. ==References== Category:Moths described in 1957 Category:Drepaninae
title: Tridrepana spatulata
